43#define HB_UNICODE_FUNCS_IMPLEMENT_CALLBACKS \
44 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (combining_class) \
45 HB_IF_NOT_DEPRECATED (HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (eastasian_width)) \
46 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (general_category) \
47 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (mirroring) \
48 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (script) \
49 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (compose) \
50 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (decompose) \
51 HB_IF_NOT_DEPRECATED (HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (decompose_compatibility)) \
52 /* ^--- Add new callbacks here */
53
54/* Simple callbacks are those taking a hb_codepoint_t and returning a hb_codepoint_t */
55#define HB_UNICODE_FUNCS_IMPLEMENT_CALLBACKS_SIMPLE \
56 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (hb_unicode_combining_class_t, combining_class) \
57 HB_IF_NOT_DEPRECATED (HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (unsigned int, eastasian_width)) \
58 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (hb_unicode_general_category_t, general_category) \
59 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (hb_codepoint_t, mirroring) \
60 HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT (hb_script_t, script) \
61 /* ^--- Add new simple callbacks here */
62
63struct hb_unicode_funcs_t
64{
65 hb_object_header_t header;
66
67 hb_unicode_funcs_t *parent;
68
69#define HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT(return_type, name) \
70 return_type name (hb_codepoint_t unicode) { return func.name (this, unicode, user_data.name); }
71HB_UNICODE_FUNCS_IMPLEMENT_CALLBACKS_SIMPLE
72#undef HB_UNICODE_FUNC_IMPLEMENT
73
74 hb_bool_t compose (hb_codepoint_t a, hb_codepoint_t b,
75 hb_codepoint_t *ab)
76 {
77 *ab = 0;
78 if (unlikely (!a || !b)) return false;
79 return func.compose (this, a, b, ab, user_data.compose);
80 }
81
82 hb_bool_t decompose (hb_codepoint_t ab,
83 hb_codepoint_t *a, hb_codepoint_t *b)
84 {
85 *a = ab; *b = 0;
86 return func.decompose (this, ab, a, b, user_data.decompose);
87 }
88
89 unsigned int decompose_compatibility (hb_codepoint_t u,
90 hb_codepoint_t *decomposed)
91 {
92#ifdef HB_DISABLE_DEPRECATED
93 unsigned int ret = 0;
94#else
95 unsigned int ret = func.decompose_compatibility (this, u, decomposed, user_data.decompose_compatibility);
96#endif
97 if (ret == 1 && u == decomposed[0]) {
98 decomposed[0] = 0;
99 return 0;
100 }
101 decomposed[ret] = 0;
102 return ret;
103 }
104
105 unsigned int
106 modified_combining_class (hb_codepoint_t u)
107 {
108 /* Reorder SAKOT to ensure it comes after any tone marks. */
109 if (unlikely (u == 0x1A60u)) return 254;
110 /* Reorder PADMA to ensure it comes after any vowel marks. */
111 if (unlikely (u == 0x0FC6u)) return 254;
112 /* Reorder TSA -PHRU to reorder before U+0F74 */
113 if (unlikely (u == 0x0F39u)) return 127;
114
115 return _hb_modified_combining_class[combining_class (unicode: u)];
116 }
117
118 static hb_bool_t
119 is_variation_selector (hb_codepoint_t unicode)
120 {
121 /* U+180B..180D, U+180F MONGOLIAN FREE VARIATION SELECTORs are handled in the
122 * Arabic shaper. No need to match them here. */
123 return unlikely (hb_in_ranges<hb_codepoint_t> (unicode,
124 0xFE00u, 0xFE0Fu, /* VARIATION SELECTOR-1..16 */
125 0xE0100u, 0xE01EFu)); /* VARIATION SELECTOR-17..256 */
126 }
127
128 /* Default_Ignorable codepoints:
129 *
130 * Note: While U+115F, U+1160, U+3164 and U+FFA0 are Default_Ignorable,
131 * we do NOT want to hide them, as the way Uniscribe has implemented them
132 * is with regular spacing glyphs, and that's the way fonts are made to work.
133 * As such, we make exceptions for those four.
134 * Also ignoring U+1BCA0..1BCA3. https://github.com/harfbuzz/harfbuzz/issues/503
135 *
136 * Unicode 14.0:
137 * $ grep '; Default_Ignorable_Code_Point ' DerivedCoreProperties.txt | sed 's/;.*#/#/'
138 * 00AD # Cf SOFT HYPHEN
139 * 034F # Mn COMBINING GRAPHEME JOINER
140 * 061C # Cf ARABIC LETTER MARK
141 * 115F..1160 # Lo [2] HANGUL CHOSEONG FILLER..HANGUL JUNGSEONG FILLER
142 * 17B4..17B5 # Mn [2] KHMER VOWEL INHERENT AQ..KHMER VOWEL INHERENT AA
143 * 180B..180D # Mn [3] MONGOLIAN FREE VARIATION SELECTOR ONE..MONGOLIAN FREE VARIATION SELECTOR THREE
144 * 180E # Cf MONGOLIAN VOWEL SEPARATOR
145 * 180F # Mn MONGOLIAN FREE VARIATION SELECTOR FOUR
146 * 200B..200F # Cf [5] ZERO WIDTH SPACE..RIGHT-TO-LEFT MARK
147 * 202A..202E # Cf [5] LEFT-TO-RIGHT EMBEDDING..RIGHT-TO-LEFT OVERRIDE
148 * 2060..2064 # Cf [5] WORD JOINER..INVISIBLE PLUS
149 * 2065 # Cn <reserved-2065>
150 * 2066..206F # Cf [10] LEFT-TO-RIGHT ISOLATE..NOMINAL DIGIT SHAPES
151 * 3164 # Lo HANGUL FILLER
152 * FE00..FE0F # Mn [16] VARIATION SELECTOR-1..VARIATION SELECTOR-16
153 * FEFF # Cf ZERO WIDTH NO-BREAK SPACE
154 * FFA0 # Lo HALFWIDTH HANGUL FILLER
155 * FFF0..FFF8 # Cn [9] <reserved-FFF0>..<reserved-FFF8>
156 * 1BCA0..1BCA3 # Cf [4] SHORTHAND FORMAT LETTER OVERLAP..SHORTHAND FORMAT UP STEP
157 * 1D173..1D17A # Cf [8] MUSICAL SYMBOL BEGIN BEAM..MUSICAL SYMBOL END PHRASE
158 * E0000 # Cn <reserved-E0000>
159 * E0001 # Cf LANGUAGE TAG
160 * E0002..E001F # Cn [30] <reserved-E0002>..<reserved-E001F>
161 * E0020..E007F # Cf [96] TAG SPACE..CANCEL TAG
162 * E0080..E00FF # Cn [128] <reserved-E0080>..<reserved-E00FF>
163 * E0100..E01EF # Mn [240] VARIATION SELECTOR-17..VARIATION SELECTOR-256
164 * E01F0..E0FFF # Cn [3600] <reserved-E01F0>..<reserved-E0FFF>
165 */
166 static hb_bool_t
167 is_default_ignorable (hb_codepoint_t ch)
168 {
169 hb_codepoint_t plane = ch >> 16;
170 if (likely (plane == 0))
171 {
172 /* BMP */
173 hb_codepoint_t page = ch >> 8;
174 switch (page) {
175 case 0x00: return unlikely (ch == 0x00ADu);
176 case 0x03: return unlikely (ch == 0x034Fu);
177 case 0x06: return unlikely (ch == 0x061Cu);
178 case 0x17: return hb_in_range<hb_codepoint_t> (u: ch, lo: 0x17B4u, hi: 0x17B5u);
179 case 0x18: return hb_in_range<hb_codepoint_t> (u: ch, lo: 0x180Bu, hi: 0x180Eu);
180 case 0x20: return hb_in_ranges<hb_codepoint_t> (u: ch, lo1: 0x200Bu, hi1: 0x200Fu,
181 ds: 0x202Au, ds: 0x202Eu,
182 ds: 0x2060u, ds: 0x206Fu);
183 case 0xFE: return hb_in_range<hb_codepoint_t> (u: ch, lo: 0xFE00u, hi: 0xFE0Fu) || ch == 0xFEFFu;
184 case 0xFF: return hb_in_range<hb_codepoint_t> (u: ch, lo: 0xFFF0u, hi: 0xFFF8u);
185 default: return false;
186 }
187 }
188 else
189 {
190 /* Other planes */
191 switch (plane) {
192 case 0x01: return hb_in_range<hb_codepoint_t> (u: ch, lo: 0x1D173u, hi: 0x1D17Au);
193 case 0x0E: return hb_in_range<hb_codepoint_t> (u: ch, lo: 0xE0000u, hi: 0xE0FFFu);
194 default: return false;
195 }
196 }
197 }

199 /* Space estimates based on:
200 * https://unicode.org/charts/PDF/U2000.pdf
201 * https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/develop/character-design-standards/whitespace
202 */
203 enum space_t {
204 NOT_SPACE = 0,
205 SPACE_EM = 1,
206 SPACE_EM_2 = 2,
207 SPACE_EM_3 = 3,
208 SPACE_EM_4 = 4,
209 SPACE_EM_5 = 5,
210 SPACE_EM_6 = 6,
211 SPACE_EM_16 = 16,
212 SPACE_4_EM_18, /* 4/18th of an EM! */
213 SPACE,
214 SPACE_FIGURE,
215 SPACE_PUNCTUATION,
216 SPACE_NARROW,
217 };
218 static space_t
219 space_fallback_type (hb_codepoint_t u)
220 {
221 switch (u)
222 {
223 /* All GC=Zs chars that can use a fallback. */
224 default: return NOT_SPACE; /* U+1680 OGHAM SPACE MARK */
225 case 0x0020u: return SPACE; /* U+0020 SPACE */
226 case 0x00A0u: return SPACE; /* U+00A0 NO-BREAK SPACE */
227 case 0x2000u: return SPACE_EM_2; /* U+2000 EN QUAD */
228 case 0x2001u: return SPACE_EM; /* U+2001 EM QUAD */
229 case 0x2002u: return SPACE_EM_2; /* U+2002 EN SPACE */
230 case 0x2003u: return SPACE_EM; /* U+2003 EM SPACE */
231 case 0x2004u: return SPACE_EM_3; /* U+2004 THREE-PER-EM SPACE */
232 case 0x2005u: return SPACE_EM_4; /* U+2005 FOUR-PER-EM SPACE */
233 case 0x2006u: return SPACE_EM_6; /* U+2006 SIX-PER-EM SPACE */
234 case 0x2007u: return SPACE_FIGURE; /* U+2007 FIGURE SPACE */
235 case 0x2008u: return SPACE_PUNCTUATION; /* U+2008 PUNCTUATION SPACE */
236 case 0x2009u: return SPACE_EM_5; /* U+2009 THIN SPACE */
237 case 0x200Au: return SPACE_EM_16; /* U+200A HAIR SPACE */
238 case 0x202Fu: return SPACE_NARROW; /* U+202F NARROW NO-BREAK SPACE */
239 case 0x205Fu: return SPACE_4_EM_18; /* U+205F MEDIUM MATHEMATICAL SPACE */
240 case 0x3000u: return SPACE_EM; /* U+3000 IDEOGRAPHIC SPACE */
241 }
242 }

261};

265/*
266 * Modified combining marks
267 */
268
269/* Hebrew
270 *
271 * We permute the "fixed-position" classes 10-26 into the order
272 * described in the SBL Hebrew manual:
273 *
274 * https://www.sbl-site.org/Fonts/SBLHebrewUserManual1.5x.pdf
275 *
276 * (as recommended by:
277 * https://forum.fontlab.com/archive-old-microsoft-volt-group/vista-and-diacritic-ordering/msg22823/)
278 *
279 * More details here:
280 * https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=662055
281 */
282#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC10 22 /* sheva */
283#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC11 15 /* hataf segol */
284#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC12 16 /* hataf patah */
285#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC13 17 /* hataf qamats */
286#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC14 23 /* hiriq */
287#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC15 18 /* tsere */
288#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC16 19 /* segol */
289#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC17 20 /* patah */
290#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC18 21 /* qamats & qamats qatan */
291#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC19 14 /* holam & holam haser for vav*/
292#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC20 24 /* qubuts */
293#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC21 12 /* dagesh */
294#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC22 25 /* meteg */
295#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC23 13 /* rafe */
296#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC24 10 /* shin dot */
297#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC25 11 /* sin dot */
298#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC26 26 /* point varika */
299
300/*
301 * Arabic
302 *
303 * Modify to move Shadda (ccc=33) before other marks. See:
304 * https://unicode.org/faq/normalization.html#8
305 * https://unicode.org/faq/normalization.html#9
306 */
307#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC27 28 /* fathatan */
308#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC28 29 /* dammatan */
309#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC29 30 /* kasratan */
310#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC30 31 /* fatha */
311#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC31 32 /* damma */
312#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC32 33 /* kasra */
313#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC33 27 /* shadda */
314#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC34 34 /* sukun */
315#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC35 35 /* superscript alef */
316
317/* Syriac */
318#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC36 36 /* superscript alaph */
319
320/* Telugu
321 *
322 * Modify Telugu length marks (ccc=84, ccc=91).
323 * These are the only matras in the main Indic scripts range that have
324 * a non-zero ccc. That makes them reorder with the Halant (ccc=9).
325 * Assign 4 and 5, which are otherwise unassigned.
326 */
327#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC84 4 /* length mark */
328#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC91 5 /* ai length mark */
329
330/* Thai
331 *
332 * Modify U+0E38 and U+0E39 (ccc=103) to be reordered before U+0E3A (ccc=9).
333 * Assign 3, which is unassigned otherwise.
334 * Uniscribe does this reordering too.
335 */
336#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC103 3 /* sara u / sara uu */
337#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC107 107 /* mai * */
338
339/* Lao */
340#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC118 118 /* sign u / sign uu */
341#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC122 122 /* mai * */
342
343/* Tibetan
344 *
345 * In case of multiple vowel-signs, use u first (but after achung)
346 * this allows Dzongkha multi-vowel shortcuts to render correctly
347 */
348#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC129 129 /* sign aa */
349#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC130 132 /* sign i */
350#define HB_MODIFIED_COMBINING_CLASS_CCC132 131 /* sign u */

368/*
369 * Ranges, used for bsearch tables.
370 */
371
372struct hb_unicode_range_t
373{
374 static int
375 cmp (const void *_key, const void *_item)
376 {
377 hb_codepoint_t cp = *((hb_codepoint_t *) _key);
378 const hb_unicode_range_t *range = (hb_unicode_range_t *) _item;
379
380 if (cp < range->start)
381 return -1;
382 else if (cp <= range->end)
383 return 0;
384 else
385 return +1;
386 }
387
388 hb_codepoint_t start;
389 hb_codepoint_t end;
390};
